486
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:22,100
Over on the bed--
the couch.

487
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:32,100
Go... Lie down.

488
00:37:36,500 --> 00:37:39,000
- Tell me when it looks right.
- Put your arm back the way it was.

489
00:37:39,500 --> 00:37:41,000
Right.

490
00:37:41,500 --> 00:37:45,000
Put that other arm up ,
that hand right by your face there.

491
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:48,000
Right.

492
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,000
Now ,  head down.

493
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:55,000
Eyes to me ,
keep them on me.

494
00:37:57,500 --> 00:37:59,000
And try to stay still.

495
00:38:02,500 --> 00:38:04,000
( Exhales)

496
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:20,000
So serious.

497
00:39:01,600 --> 00:39:05,100
I believe you are blushing ,
Mr. Big Artiste.

498
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:12,100
I can't imagine
Monsieur Monet blushing.

499
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:17,100
He does landscapes.
Just relax your face.

500
00:39:17,600 --> 00:39:19,100
- Sorry.
- No laughing.

501
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:22,100
( Exhales)

502
00:39:50,500 --> 00:39:54,000
My heart was pounding
the whole time.

503
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:58,000
It was the most erotic moment
of my life.

504
00:40:01,500 --> 00:40:04,000
Up until then ,  at least.

505
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:10,000
- So what happened next?
- You mean ,  did we do it?

506
00:40:12,500 --> 00:40:14,000
Sorry ,  to disappoint you ,
Mr. Bodine.

507
00:40:14,500 --> 00:40:17,000
Jack was very professional.

508
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:28,100
Thank you.

509
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:31,100
( Rose Laughing)

510
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:36,100
What you doing?

511
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,100
Will you put this back
in the safe for me?

512
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:40,100
Mm-hmm.

513
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:53,100
Would you excuse me?

514
00:40:55,600 --> 00:41:00,100
- None of the stewards have seen her.
- This is absurd.

515
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:03,100
It's a ship ,  there's only
so many places she could be.

516
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:05,100
Lovejoy ,  find her.

517
00:41:23,500 --> 00:41:25,000
- Clear.
- Yes.

518
00:41:25,500 --> 00:41:30,000
I don't think I've ever seen
such a flat calm.

519
00:41:30,500 --> 00:41:34,000
Like a mill pond.
Not a breath of wind.

520
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:38,000
It will make the bergs
harder to see

521
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:42,000
with no breaking water
at the base.

522
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:44,000
Hmm.

523
00:41:51,500 --> 00:41:56,000
Well ,  I'm off. Maintain speed
and heading ,  Mr. Lightoller.

524
00:41:56,500 --> 00:41:58,000
Yes ,  sir.

525
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,100
It's getting cold.
You look nice.

526
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:13,100
- ( Knock At Door)
- Lovejoy: Miss Rose?

527
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,100
My drawings!

528
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,100
( Door Closes)

529
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:43,100
Come on!

530
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:49,100
- No ,  wait ,  wait!
- Wait ,  wait ,  wait!

531
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:51,100
Go ,  go! Down ,  down!

532
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:55,100
Rose:
Quickly ,  quickly!

533
00:42:57,600 --> 00:42:59,100
( Giggling)
Bye!

534
00:43:07,500 --> 00:43:09,000
- Sorry!
- ( Giggling)

535
00:43:14,500 --> 00:43:18,000
- It's all right!
- ( Laughing)

536
00:43:26,500 --> 00:43:28,000
Pretty tough for a valet ,
this fellow.

537
00:43:28,500 --> 00:43:31,000
- Seems more like a cop.
- I think he was.

538
00:43:31,500 --> 00:43:33,000
-Jack: Oh ,  shit.
- ( Rose Screams)

539
00:43:38,500 --> 00:43:40,000
No ,  over here!

540
00:43:40,500 --> 00:43:42,000
Quick!

541
00:43:45,500 --> 00:43:48,000
( Boiler Blasting)

542
00:43:48,500 --> 00:43:51,000
- Now what?!
- What?!

543
00:43:58,600 --> 00:44:01,100
Hold up! What're you two
doing down here?

544
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:05,100
You shouldn't be down here!
It could be dangerous!

545
00:44:07,600 --> 00:44:11,100
Jack: Carry on! Don't mind us.
You're doing a great job!

546
00:44:11,600 --> 00:44:13,100
Keep up the good work!

547
00:44:29,600 --> 00:44:32,100
Ah ,  look what
we have here ,  huh?

548
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:45,100
( Rose Clears Throat)

549
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:51,100
Thank you.

550
00:45:01,500 --> 00:45:05,000
- ( Honks Horn)
- Where to ,  miss?

551
00:45:05,500 --> 00:45:07,000
To the stars.

552
00:45:26,500 --> 00:45:28,000
You nervous?

553
00:45:30,500 --> 00:45:33,000
No.

554
00:45:48,600 --> 00:45:51,100
Put your hands on me , Jack.

555
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:16,100
Crewman:
God ,  it's bloody cold.

556
00:46:16,600 --> 00:46:21,100
You know ,  I can smell ice ,
you know ,  when it's near.

557
00:46:21,600 --> 00:46:25,100
- Bollocks.
- But I can ,  all right!

558
00:46:25,600 --> 00:46:28,100
Murdoch: Did you ever find
those binoculars for the lookouts?

559
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:30,100
Haven't seen them
since Southampton.

560
00:46:30,600 --> 00:46:33,100
Well ,  I'll be on my rounds.
Cheerio.

561
00:47:04,500 --> 00:47:06,000
You're trembling.

562
00:47:07,500 --> 00:47:11,000
Don't worry.
I'll be all right.

563
00:47:31,500 --> 00:47:35,000
- They ran down there.
- Right.

564
00:47:44,600 --> 00:47:46,100
Lovejoy:
Anything missing?

565
00:48:11,600 --> 00:48:13,100
I've got a better idea.

566
00:48:24,600 --> 00:48:26,100
Gotcha!

567
00:48:28,600 --> 00:48:32,100
( Rose Laughing)

568
00:48:33,500 --> 00:48:36,000
( Laughing)

569
00:48:36,500 --> 00:48:39,000
Did you see those guys' faces?

570
00:48:39,500 --> 00:48:42,000
Did you see the...

571
00:48:47,500 --> 00:48:50,000
When the ship docks...

572
00:48:50,500 --> 00:48:52,000
I'm getting off with you.

573
00:48:52,500 --> 00:48:55,000
This is crazy.

574
00:48:55,500 --> 00:48:58,000
I know.
It doesn't make any sense.

575
00:48:59,500 --> 00:49:01,000
That's why I trust it.

576
00:49:09,500 --> 00:49:12,000
( Quietly):
Oh , yes. Here ,  look at this.

577
00:49:13,500 --> 00:49:15,000
Oh ,  look at that ,  would you?

578
00:49:15,500 --> 00:49:19,000
- They're a bit warmer than we are.
- Well ,  if that's what it takes

579
00:49:19,500 --> 00:49:22,000
for us to get warmer I'd rather not ,
if it's all the same to you.

580
00:49:33,600 --> 00:49:37,100
- Bugger me!
- ( Alarm Bell Clanging)

581
00:49:39,600 --> 00:49:42,100
- ( Phone Rings)
- Pick up , you bastards!

582
00:49:42,600 --> 00:49:45,100
( Phone Ringing)

583
00:49:45,600 --> 00:49:48,100
- Is there anyone there?
- Yes ,  what Do you see?

584
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:53,100
- Iceberg! Right ahead!
- Thank you.

585
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:56,100
Iceberg! Right ahead!
Hard to starboard!

586
00:49:56,600 --> 00:49:58,100
Crewman:
Hard to starboard!

587
00:50:02,600 --> 00:50:06,100
- ( Ringing)
- Crewman: Turn ,  turn! Steady!

588
00:50:07,600 --> 00:50:10,100
- ( Ringing)
- ( Bell Clangs )

589
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:12,100
Full astern!

